### Testing and Building

```bash
# Run Jest tests
yarn nx test <project>                                    # Run all tests for a project
yarn nx test <project> --testFile=<path/to/file.spec.ts> # Run a specific test file (faster, recommended)
yarn nx test <project> --testPathPattern="<pattern>"      # Run tests matching pattern (runs all tests, slower)

# Other commands
yarn nx lint <project>        # ESLint with auto-fix
yarn nx tsc <project>         # Type-check without emit
yarn nx build <project>       # Build for production

# Run multiple projects
yarn nx run-many --target=test --projects=legal-gazette-api,legal-gazette-web
```

**Testing Best Practice**: When running specific test files, use `--testFile` instead of `--testPathPattern`. The `--testFile` flag runs only the specified file, while `--testPathPattern` runs all tests first then filters, which is much slower.

